title: For Trade:  .22 ammo for Silver coins (don't roll your eyes)
postcontent:
This isn't going to be anyone's favorite post, but I am looking to trade .22 ammo for silver coins.  Believe me, I will definitely shoot all the ammo I have - I only have a .22 and .40, so nothing will be wasted.  But with the spot price of silver at just under $21, I can afford to try to add to my daughter's collection.  I'm not going to try to screw you on the prices; if you're not sure of the value of what you have, check eBay.  If I had a choice in the matter, I would be looking for Morgan's ("O" mint mark, because New Orleans is special to me), Canadian Maple Leaf, and Chinese Panda's.  There are so many gaps in our collection that almost everything fits.  Only in 2013 was I able to complete the entire World collection (that's China, Fiji, USA, Andorra, New Zealand, Canada, United Kingdom, and other numismatic silver producing countries, maybe 13 or 14 total).  American Eagle Proofs rock.

Got a random silver coin in the drawer? Let me know what you have (pictures help) and let's see what we can do.  Most interested in numismatic coins, but ingots and bullion can be considered.  We're not going to melt anything.  Of course I am interested in gold coins - who wouldn't be? - but I am pretty sure I can only make an offer on a $5 coin, nowhere near a $20 or $50 piece.

On the table are Federal Blue Box bulk, CCI Blazers / Velocitors / Stingers / Standard, Remington Golden Bullets. .40's if that's your thing.

FTF Charlotte, Belmont, Gastonia, Kings Mountain.

Text me at Six-one-5 8-two-8 7-nine-2-nine

title: For Sale/Trade:  Coxoncall, give it a rest!
postcontent:
As a regular armslist user, just wanted to send a shoutout to you Matt, or coxoncall.

I get it, guns aren't always cheap and most of us don't have several hundred dollars lying around that we can drop on guns whenever we want, even if we'd like to.  But most of us are here to buy, sell, and trade FIREARMS, not random household and lawn/garden stuff.

Normally I wouldn't bother saying anything, but when I get that same list of random stuff emailed to me EVERY TIME i post something, it gets old.  I get the impression that you're on here a lot and appreciate firearms, which is great, but most of us just aren't interested.  If you have so much stuff that you have no use for I imagine having a garage sale would be your best bet to get rid of it and get the cash you need to buy the guns you're looking for.

Anyway, I'm not looking to be mean or publicly shame anybody, but just thought I would say what no doubt many of us here on armslist are thinking.

Respectfully,
A fellow Wichita Armslist user.
